<doc id="1228247" wikidata="Q172518" url="?curid=1228247" title="Brausch Niemann">
<text>Ambraüsus &quot;Brausch&quot; Niemann (born 7 January 1939) is a former racing driver from South Africa. He participated in 2 Formula One World Championship Grands Prix in 1963 and 1965, both in his home country, driving a privately entered Lotus. He managed to qualify for the first of these, finishing 14th and scoring no championship points.

After success in Formula Junior in the mid-1960s, Niemann switched to enduro motor cycle racing, winning the South African championship in 1979.

